defaults understanding of what they
default’
defaultre looking for in a surgeon, an engineer, a mathematician or a chemist are also tied up with people
default’
defaults assumptions around gender 
default–
default the assumed 
defaultidentity of an academic in STEMM tends to be linked to masculinity. This is also similar for leadership roles 
default–
default the skills or abilities that people think they need in a leader or a manager are also connected to a normative masculine identity, and women who
default display these skills are often judged negatively because they are perceived to be presenting stereotypically masculine traits. Conversely, women who don
default’
defaultt display these traits may be viewed as unsuitable for the role.  
defaultThese assumptions can also lead to w
defaultomen being given ‘pastoral’ roles within departments, such as teaching and student support roles. This often means that men have more time to focus on research activities – which are more likely to lead to a promotion. 
