default‘Attending institutions with m
defaultore female professors strengthens female students' scholarly confidence, motivation to achieve, and grade-point average. Yet the presence of female professors appears to bring a broader range of benefits to male students, including gains in mathematical co
defaultnfidence, scientific orientation, leadership ability, and emotional well-being. An obvious implication of those findings would be for colleges to hire more female faculty members. That could be an opportunity to shape the academic climate, as female facult
defaulty members have been shown to be generally more concerned than male faculty members with students' emotional development, character development, and self-understanding’ 
